1
00:00:02,210 --> 00:00:06,880
So, Yuki and Makoto-kun
were actually childhood friends?

2
00:00:06,880 --> 00:00:10,800
Makoto-kun's grandma's house
was right near ours.

3
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:14,100
Oh, I had no idea
you two go to the same university.

4
00:00:14,100 --> 00:00:15,930
You've grown so much.

5
00:00:15,930 --> 00:00:19,390
After my grandma passed away,
I stopped going over there.

6
00:00:19,810 --> 00:00:23,440
I can't believe Yuki
is the same "Yu-kun" from back then.

7
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:27,740
That said, it's pretty wild
not to recognize your own childhood friend.

8
00:00:27,740 --> 00:00:31,240
Well, once they get taller,
they can be totally unrecognizable.

9
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:35,370
Look at how stylish Yuki is now.
He's like a completely different person, isn't he?

10
00:00:35,370 --> 00:00:37,000
His makeup skills are really amazing.

11
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,080
Yeah, they really are.

12
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:43,540
I think it's great,
but his dad...

13
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:48,840
Yuki's dad...
I remember him being pretty strict.

14
00:00:49,470 --> 00:00:52,140
Don't tell me he found out
about the suspension?

15
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:57,180
Yeah, the school called,
and now it's chaos at his house.

16
00:00:57,180 --> 00:01:01,480
His dad said that until Yuki learns his lesson,
he's not allowed to contact any of his friends.

17
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:04,440
That's why I rushed to bring his things over.

18
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:06,480
I see.

19
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:11,530
Oh, shoot.
I should get going. It was nice seeing you.

20
00:01:11,530 --> 00:01:13,780
Take care on your way home.

21
00:01:14,740 --> 00:01:21,040
Oh, by the way, Makoto-kun.
Is the cut on your ear okay? You're alright?
